# UI Restyle Safety Constraints

Apply to every visual restyle (colors, borders, spacing, typography). **Screen styles only.**

## Scrolling

- Do NOT change the flex/overflow/height structure of scroll containers. Preserve every existing `min-h-0`, `overflow-hidden`, `overflow-auto`, `flex-1`, `h-full`.
- If a scroll region breaks, the layout skeleton must stay identical — only colors, borders, spacing, and typography change; never the flex/overflow topology.
- Sticky table headers: `position: sticky` inside the **existing** scroll container. Do not introduce a new scroll parent.

## Printing (critical)

- Do NOT touch `@media print` CSS, print-specific components, PRN/TSPL generators, or barcode label rendering. These are separate from screen styles.
- New chrome colors (navy, dark footers, etc.) must NOT leak into print. Verify `@media print` still forces white background / black text where needed. Print output must be **byte-identical** to before the change.
- Do NOT restyle `SchoolFeeReceipt`, tax invoice print views, barcode label templates, or thermal receipt layouts.

## Fixed / sticky + z-index

- Keep the existing z-index scale. Sticky header/footer must not overlap dialogs, dropdowns, the tab bar, or the sidebar.
- Verify dropdowns/comboboxes still render above the sticky header.

## Dialogs

- Do not change dialog/modal/backdrop z-index or portal behavior.

## Responsive

- Dense layouts must still work on Capacitor (mobile) and small Electron windows — fields wrap/stack; no overflow or clip.

## Verify before done

- [ ] Long list/grid scrolls smoothly; header/footer stay fixed.
- [ ] Print an invoice, a barcode label, and an A4 tax invoice — output **unchanged**.
- [ ] Open every dialog on the page — renders correctly, above content.
- [ ] Resize window small + mobile view — no clipping/overflow.
